# Lab 2 - Basic Network Information in Ubuntu

## Objective

Learn how to view network information using Linux commands.

## Commands Used

```bash
hostname
hostname -I
ip addr
ip route
ping 8.8.8.8
ping google.com
```

## What I Learned

- Every computer has a hostname.
- My Ubuntu VM received an IP address.
- The routing table shows the default gateway.
- `ping` tests network connectivity.
- DNS translates domain names into IP addresses.
 # Lab 3 - Basic Network Diagnostics in Ubuntu

## Objective
Learn how to inspect network configuration and test connectivity.

## Commands Used

```bash
hostname
hostname -I
ip addr
ip route
ping google.com
ping 8.8.8.8
nslookup google.com
traceroute google.com
```

## Results
- Verified hostname.
- Identified the VM's IP address.
- Found the default gateway.
- Confirmed Internet connectivity.
- Verified DNS name resolution.
- Observed the route to a remote server.

## Skills Gained
- Basic network troubleshooting
- Reading network configuration
- Testing DNS
- Verifying connectivity
